<A> Ala Alanine         (H) -CH₃
<B> Asx Asparagine or Aspartic Acid
<C> Cys Cysteine        ( ) -CH₂-<S>H
<D> Asp Aspartic Acid   (-) -CH₂-CO₂
<E> Glu Glutamic Acid   (-) -CH₂-CH₂-CO₂
<F> Phe Phenylalanine  E(H) -CH₂-Phenyl
<G> Gly Glycine         ( ) -H
<H> His Histidine      E(+) -CH₂-Imidazole
<I> Ile Isoleucine     E(H) -C(CH₃)-CH₂-CH₃
<J> Xle Leucine or Isoleucine
<K> Lys Lysine         E(+) -CH₂-CH₂-CH₂-CH₂-<N>H₃
<L> Leu Leucine        E(H) -CH₂-C(CH₃)₂
<M> Met Methionine     E(+) -CH₂-CH₂-<S>-CH₃
<N> Asn Asparagine      (P) -CH₂-CO-<N>H₂
<O> Pyl Pyrrolysine     (?) -CH₂-CH₂-CH₂-CH₂-<N>H-CO-Pyrroline
<P> Pro Proline         ( ) -CH₂-CH₂-CH₂- (cyclic connection to N)
<Q> Gln Glutamine       (P) -CH₂-CH₂-CO-<N>H₂
<R> Arg Arginine        (+) -CH₂-CH₂-CH₂-<N>H-C(<N>H₂)₂
<S> Ser Serine          (P) -CH₂-OH
<T> Thr Threonine      E(P) -CH(CH₃)-OH
<U> Sec Selenocysteine  ( ) -CH₂-<Se>H
<V> Val Valine         E(H) -CH(CH₃)₂
<W> Trp Tryptophan     E(H) -CH₂-Indole
<Y> Tyr Tyrosine        (H) -CH₂-Phenyl-OH
<X> Xaa Unknown, used when amino acid doesn't matter
<Z> Glx Glutamine or Glutamic Acid
| E = essential, + = positive/acidic, - = negative/basic
| H = hydrophobic, P = polar/uncharged
